<shortcontents class="MCRMetaLangText" heritable="false" notinherit="false"><shortcontent xml:lang="en" inherited="0" form="plain">I) Täʾamrä Maryam “Miracles of Mary” (fols. 3ra-54ra)&#13;
I-1) Mäṣḥafä śǝrʿat, Introductory rite of al-Muʿallaqah (fols. 3ra-7va)&#13;
I-2) Introductory exhortation (fols. 7ra-10vb)&#13;
I-3) ʾƎsäggǝd läki wä-ʾǝweddǝsäki … “I worship Thee…” (fols. 10vb-12rb)&#13;
I-4) Täʾamrä Maryam: 29 partly numbered miracles (fols. 12rb-53rb, 54ra)&#13;
I-5) ʾAkkonu bǝʾǝsi… “Does not the man…” (distributed among the miracles of Mary, fols. 15rb-52vb)&#13;
&#13;
Additiones 1-2.</shortcontent>
</shortcontents>
