<txstates class="MCRMetaLangText" heritable="false" notinherit="false"><txstate xml:lang="en" inherited="0" form="plain">The leather cover is severely torn off from the back board and is damaged along the corners of the front board. The spine cover is missing, probably cut off to facilitate resewing.&#13;
Textile inlay on the inner side of the left cover is missing.&#13;
The Ms. has been resewn and the sewing has been replaced with several modern synthetic threads.&#13;
Many fols. are misplaced, some are possibly missing.&#13;
Many leaves are stained with water: e.g., fols. 7r, 14r, 20v, 28r, 54r.&#13;
Text on some leaves is barely legible due to faded ink: e.g., fols. 3r, 8rb, 16vb, 34ra.&#13;
Fols. 1-2 are undersized and serve as endleaves.&#13;
Some leaves are held together by means of one-stitched repair (e.g., fols. 25-32 and fols. 33-54).&#13;
Tears amended on fols. 36, 41.</txstate>
</txstates>
