<otherdetails class="MCRMetaLangText" heritable="false" notinherit="false"><otherdetail xml:lang="en" inherited="0" form="plain">Text I-2 includes the hymns:&#13;
- ʾO-ʾәgzǝʾtǝyä qǝddǝst dǝngǝl bä-kǝlʾe Maryam ʾǝmmu lä-ʾIyäsus kähali … "O my Lady, Holy Two-fold Virgin Mary, mother of Jesus the Almighty ..." (fols. 9rb-va),&#13;
- Sälam läki ʾo-ʾәgzǝʾtǝyä Maryam dǝngǝl ʾǝmmä bǝrhan wä-ʾǝmmä nädd... "Salutation to you, o my Lady, Virgin Mary, Mother of the Light and Mother of the Flame ..." (fols. 9va-10vb).&#13;
Some miracles are not numbered. The first miracle is followed by the hymn: Sobä ṣäḥafä Däqsǝyos täʾamriha ʿǝludä ... "When Däqsǝyos wrote the collection of her miracles ..." (fol. 14va).&#13;
Text I-5 comprises 25 strophes which are strophes 2-10, 12-27 according to GrohHymn pp. 336-53.</otherdetail>
</otherdetails>
